23/03/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- A team of US military experts is expected to arrive in Bulgaria by the end of the week for talks on the possible relocation of US military bases to the country's territory, Deputy Defence Minister Ilko Dimitrov said Monday (22 March). 
According to Dimitrov, the proposal under consideration would involve the deployment of small bases, allowing rotation and mobility of troops and infrastructure.
In other news Monday, Bulgaria and Romania affirmed the need for a co-operation agreement aimed at bolstering security along their common border. 
Joint patrols would guard strategic facilities situated along the border. 
(BTA, Rompres - 22/03/04)
